taRobots&quot;:&quot;index, follow&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:0},&quot;lastPostId&quot;:&quot;9030&quot;},{&quot;firstPost&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:851,&quot;author&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:3479,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/members\/user831-3479&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;User831&quot;,&quot;avatar&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userTitle&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userLevel&quot;:0},&quot;content&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;I noticed that adding intercom-ios takes an awfully long time to fetch repository. Upon further inspection it looks like the repo is ~1.5GB in size.&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a0&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Swift package manager for some reason chooses to fetch the entire directory and therefore it takes an inordinate amount of time to download (over 8minutes).&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=\&quot;https:\/\/uploads-eu-west-1.insided.com\/intercom-en\/attachment\/0682G00000DvhT6QAJ.png\&quot;&gt;&lt;\/img&gt;&lt;\/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/long-time-to-fetch-intercom-ios-repository-with-spm-851&quot;,&quot;creationDate&quot;:&quot;2021-06-29T14:42:23+0000&quot;,&quot;relativeCreationDate&quot;:&quot;2 years ago&quot;},&quot;isTopicUnread&quot;:true,&quot;privateId&quot;:812,&quot;id&quot;:851,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;post&quot;,&quot;hasCurrentUserLiked&quot;:false,&quot;isSticky&quot;:false,&quot;features&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;isAnswered&quot;,&quot;label&quot;:&quot;beantwoord&quot;}],&quot;forum&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:24,&quot;isIdeation&quot;:false,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/mobile-sdks-24&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Mobile SDKs&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Engage users of your mobile app with an onboarding and support experience powered by DAST&quot;},&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/long-time-to-fetch-intercom-ios-repository-with-spm-851&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Long time to fetch intercom-ios repository with SPM&quot;,&quot;lastPost&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:9027,&quot;author&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:1257,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/members\/brian-b11-1257&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Brian B11&quot;,&quot;avatar&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userTitle&quot;:&quot;Employee&quot;,&quot;rank&quot;:{&quot;isBold&quot;:false,&quot;isItalic&quot;:false,&quot;isUnderline&quot;:false,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Employee&quot;},&quot;userLevel&quot;:0},&quot;content&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/long-time-to-fetch-intercom-ios-repository-with-spm-851?postid=15804#post15804&quot;,&quot;creationDate&quot;:&quot;2023-07-10T09:19:58+0000&quot;,&quot;relativeCreationDate&quot;:&quot;3 hours ago&quot;},&quot;numberOfUnreadReplies&quot;:0,&quot;numberOfReplies&quot;:9,&quot;numberOfLikes&quot;:0,&quot;relevantPost&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:851,&quot;author&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:3479,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/members\/user831-3479&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;User831&quot;,&quot;avatar&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userTitle&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userLevel&quot;:0},&quot;content&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;I noticed that adding intercom-ios takes an awfully long time to fetch repository. Upon further inspection it looks like the repo is ~1.5GB in size.&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u00a0&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Swift package manager for some reason chooses to fetch the entire directory and therefore it takes an inordinate amount of time to download (over 8minutes).&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=\&quot;https:\/\/uploads-eu-west-1.insided.com\/intercom-en\/attachment\/0682G00000DvhT6QAJ.png\&quot;&gt;&lt;\/img&gt;&lt;\/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/long-time-to-fetch-intercom-ios-repository-with-spm-851&quot;,&quot;creationDate&quot;:&quot;2021-06-29T14:42:23+0000&quot;,&quot;relativeCreationDate&quot;:&quot;2 years ago&quot;},&quot;numberOfViews&quot;:53,&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;question&quot;,&quot;featuredImage&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;publicLabel&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;category&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/popular-topics-20&quot;,&quot;categoryId&quot;:20,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Popular Topics&quot;,&quot;metaRobots&quot;:&quot;index, follow&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:0},&quot;lastPostId&quot;:&quot;9027&quot;},{&quot;firstPost&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:2369,&quot;author&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:6941,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/members\/user1873-6941&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;User1873&quot;,&quot;avatar&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userTitle&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userLevel&quot;:0},&quot;content&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;Hi everyone, since SPM loads a full mirror of the repository it needs to fetch ~1.5GB of data before a build can start. On a developer machine I don&amp;#39;t care to much about that. A lot of it is cached, so its not like I have to pull the repo every time.&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u200b&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;BUT:&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u200b&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The loading of the DAST SDK SPM on our CI takes a very long time, since it needs to pull a fresh repo mirror everytime it runs. By far the most time of any of our packages which we load. And since we pay per minute this really increases our costs. &lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Other SDKs like Stripe (&lt;a href=\&quot;https:\/\/github.com\/stripe\/stripe-ios-spm\&quot; target=\&quot;_blank\&quot;&gt;https:\/\/github.com\/stripe\/stripe-ios-spm&lt;\/a&gt; and Klarna (&lt;a href=\&quot;https:\/\/github.com\/klarna\/klarna-mobile-sdk-spm\&quot; target=\&quot;_blank\&quot;&gt;https:\/\/github.com\/klarna\/klarna-mobile-sdk-spm&lt;\/a&gt; have created lightweight mirrors of the SDK that just contain the Sources and Binaries in tagged releases. Would this be a something you could consider?&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u200b&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This would save us a lot of time and money during our CI runtime.&lt;\/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/loading-of-intercom-sdk-via-swift-package-manager-takes-very-long-on-ci-2369&quot;,&quot;creationDate&quot;:&quot;2022-09-08T07:14:19+0000&quot;,&quot;relativeCreationDate&quot;:&quot;10 months ago&quot;},&quot;isTopicUnread&quot;:true,&quot;privateId&quot;:2214,&quot;id&quot;:2369,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;post&quot;,&quot;hasCurrentUserLiked&quot;:false,&quot;isSticky&quot;:false,&quot;features&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:&quot;isAnswered&quot;,&quot;label&quot;:&quot;beantwoord&quot;}],&quot;forum&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:24,&quot;isIdeation&quot;:false,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/mobile-sdks-24&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Mobile SDKs&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;Engage users of your mobile app with an onboarding and support experience powered by DAST&quot;},&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/loading-of-intercom-sdk-via-swift-package-manager-takes-very-long-on-ci-2369&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Loading of DAST SDK via Swift Package Manager takes very long on CI&quot;,&quot;lastPost&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:9026,&quot;author&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:1257,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/members\/brian-b11-1257&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Brian B11&quot;,&quot;avatar&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userTitle&quot;:&quot;Employee&quot;,&quot;rank&quot;:{&quot;isBold&quot;:false,&quot;isItalic&quot;:false,&quot;isUnderline&quot;:false,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Employee&quot;},&quot;userLevel&quot;:0},&quot;content&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/loading-of-intercom-sdk-via-swift-package-manager-takes-very-long-on-ci-2369?postid=15803#post15803&quot;,&quot;creationDate&quot;:&quot;2023-07-10T09:19:36+0000&quot;,&quot;relativeCreationDate&quot;:&quot;3 hours ago&quot;},&quot;numberOfUnreadReplies&quot;:0,&quot;numberOfReplies&quot;:7,&quot;numberOfLikes&quot;:0,&quot;relevantPost&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:2369,&quot;author&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:6941,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/members\/user1873-6941&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;User1873&quot;,&quot;avatar&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userTitle&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;userLevel&quot;:0},&quot;content&quot;:&quot;&lt;p&gt;Hi everyone, since SPM loads a full mirror of the repository it needs to fetch ~1.5GB of data before a build can start. On a developer machine I don&amp;#39;t care to much about that. A lot of it is cached, so its not like I have to pull the repo every time.&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u200b&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;BUT:&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u200b&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The loading of the DAST SDK SPM on our CI takes a very long time, since it needs to pull a fresh repo mirror everytime it runs. By far the most time of any of our packages which we load. And since we pay per minute this really increases our costs. &lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Other SDKs like Stripe (&lt;a href=\&quot;https:\/\/github.com\/stripe\/stripe-ios-spm\&quot; target=\&quot;_blank\&quot;&gt;https:\/\/github.com\/stripe\/stripe-ios-spm&lt;\/a&gt; and Klarna (&lt;a href=\&quot;https:\/\/github.com\/klarna\/klarna-mobile-sdk-spm\&quot; target=\&quot;_blank\&quot;&gt;https:\/\/github.com\/klarna\/klarna-mobile-sdk-spm&lt;\/a&gt; have created lightweight mirrors of the SDK that just contain the Sources and Binaries in tagged releases. Would this be a something you could consider?&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\u200b&lt;\/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This would save us a lot of time and money during our CI runtime.&lt;\/p&gt;&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\/\/community.intercom.com\/mobile-sdks-24\/loading-of-intercom-sdk-via-swift-package-manager-takes-very-long-on-ci-2369&quot;,&quot;creationDate&quot;:&quot;2022-09-08T07:14:19+0000&quot;,&quot;relativeCreationDate&quot;:&quot;10 months ago&quot;},&quot;numberOfViews&quot;:79,&quot;contentType&quot;:&quot;question&quot;,&quot;featuredImage&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;publicLabel&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;category&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;\/popular-topics-20&quot;,&quot;categoryId&quot;:20,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Popular Topics&quot;,&quot;metaRobots&quot;:&quot;index, follow&quot;,&quot;type&quot;:0},&quot;lastPostId&quot;:&quot;9026&quot;},{&quot;fir